Items.ItemValue: Option 1: Hard Non-Duplication: Determine what Anthem would have paid had we been the primary carrier then subtract the other carrierӳ paid amount.
Items.ItemText: Option 1: Hard Non-Duplication: Determine what Anthem would have paid had we been the primary carrier then subtract the other carrierӳ paid amount.

Items.ItemValue: Option 2: Standard COB up to Anthem allowed:  Use Anthem allowed amount to determine Anthemӳ liability.  If Anthemӳ liability is greater than what Anthem would have paid as primary, we will pay what we would have had Anthem been primary. However, if our liability is less than what Anthem would have paid as primary, then Anthem pays the lesser of the two amounts.
Items.ItemText: Option 2: Standard COB up to Anthem allowed:  Use Anthem allowed amount to determine Anthemӳ liability.  If Anthemӳ liability is greater than what Anthem would have paid as primary, we will pay what we would have had Anthem been primary. However, if our liability is less than what Anthem would have paid as primary, then Anthem pays the lesser of the two amounts.

Items.ItemValue: Option 3: Soft Non-Duplication: Subtract the other carrier's payment from the allowance and then apply Anthem's benefits. (Benefit calculations done after COB application.) USED w/ CDHP products.
Items.ItemText: Option 3: Soft Non-Duplication: Subtract the other carrier's payment from the allowance and then apply Anthem's benefits. (Benefit calculations done after COB application.) USED w/ CDHP products.

Items.ItemValue: Option 4: Standard COB-Up to Higher Allowed: Use the higher amount (Anthem or other carrier) to determine Anthemӳ liability. If Anthemӳ liability is greater than what Anthem would have paid as primary, we will pay what we would have had Anthem been primary. However, if our liability is less than what Anthem would have paid as primary, then we pay our liability.
Items.ItemText: Option 4: Standard COB-Up to Higher Allowed: Use the higher amount (Anthem or other carrier) to determine Anthemӳ liability. If Anthemӳ liability is greater than what Anthem would have paid as primary, we will pay what we would have had Anthem been primary. However, if our liability is less than what Anthem would have paid as primary, then we pay our liability.

Items.ItemValue: Option 5: Standard COB-Up to Billed Amount: Use billed charge to determine Anthemӳ liability. If Anthemӳ liability is greater than what Anthem would have paid as primary, we will pay what we would have had Anthem been primary. However, if our liability is less than what Anthem would have paid as primary, then we pay our liability.
Items.ItemText: Option 5: Standard COB-Up to Billed Amount: Use billed charge to determine Anthemӳ liability. If Anthemӳ liability is greater than what Anthem would have paid as primary, we will pay what we would have had Anthem been primary. However, if our liability is less than what Anthem would have paid as primary, then we pay our liability.

Elements.Name: ANT1316TextBox55595
Elements.Label: The following rules determine the order in which benefits are payable:

Items.ItemValue: Option 1: Soft Non-Duplication - Medicare is carved out prior to determining Anthemӳ benefit.
Items.ItemText: Option 1: Soft Non-Duplication - Medicare is carved out prior to determining Anthemӳ benefit.

Items.ItemValue: Option 2: Hard Non-Duplication - Medicare is carved out after Anthemӳ benefit has been determined.
Items.ItemText: Option 2: Hard Non-Duplication - Medicare is carved out after Anthemӳ benefit has been determined.

Items.ItemValue: Option 3: Medicare is carved out prior to Anthemӳ benefit determination and all of Anthemӳ out of pocket maximums (deductibles and coinsurance must be met prior to any payment being made by Anthem. determining Anthemӳ benefit.
Items.ItemText: Option 3: Medicare is carved out prior to Anthemӳ benefit determination and all of Anthemӳ out of pocket maximums (deductibles and coinsurance must be met prior to any payment being made by Anthem. determining Anthemӳ benefit.

Items.ItemValue: Option 4: Medicare is carved out prior to determining Anthemӳ benefit, but Medicare claims are not subject to deductible and coinsurance. If Medicare denies and services are covered under Anthem's group benefits then Anthem will pay.
Items.ItemText: Option 4: Medicare is carved out prior to determining Anthemӳ benefit, but Medicare claims are not subject to deductible and coinsurance. If Medicare denies and services are covered under Anthem's group benefits then Anthem will pay.

Items.ItemValue: Option 5: Standard COB w/Medicare with Benefit Reserve -  When Anthem pays as the secondary carrier to Medicare, the payment is equal to the Anthem allowed amount minus any amount paid by Medicare.  The payment should not exceed what Anthem would have paid as primary.  Benefit reserve is a coordination of benefits (COB) savings that is determined by the secondary plan by subtracting the actual amount that it paid (as secondary) from the amount it would have paid had it been primary. When Anthem is the secondary plan, these savings are recorded as a reserve and used to pay any allowable expenses, not otherwise paid, that are incurred by the enrollee during the claim determination period.
Items.ItemText: Option 5: Standard COB w/Medicare with Benefit Reserve -  When Anthem pays as the secondary carrier to Medicare, the payment is equal to the Anthem allowed amount minus any amount paid by Medicare.  The payment should not exceed what Anthem would have paid as primary.  Benefit reserve is a coordination of benefits (COB) savings that is determined by the secondary plan by subtracting the actual amount that it paid (as secondary) from the amount it would have paid had it been primary. When Anthem is the secondary plan, these savings are recorded as a reserve and used to pay any allowable expenses, not otherwise paid, that are incurred by the enrollee during the claim determination period.
